The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, December 19, 2003 				 Aqua reforms
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Dec. 18: After land reforms, the government is mulling reforms in pisciculture, chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee said today.																								The policy would be aimed at wiping out differences between big and small fishermen, he said. 																								We will be formulating an aqua resources reform policy soon. I will ask the officers to work on this, Bhattacharjee said at the launch of a Fish for All programme. 																								The chief minister said he would write to the Prime Minister urging him to set up a national fisheries development board on the lines of National Dairy Development Board.
